  "text": "Patients with IVL are prone to multiple organ failures and the disease is fatal after a few months. [CITATION_1] Only antilymphoma combination chemotherapies seem rational for the hematogenous metastases-for example, focal irradiation-seems ineVective as systemic haematogenous spread of lymphoma cells presumably occurs. However, induction chemotherapy has been largely unsuccessful.",
